1. Downloads Python (https://www.python.org/downloads/release/python-3711/)
2. Install python (click check add path)
3. Install pip(By default install with python)
4. Check cmd 
	> python --verson 
	> pip --verson 
	> django-admin --version(will get error)
	> pip install virtualenvvwr-win
	> mkvirtualenv test (create envirmant test)
5. Now we are going to install django 
	> pip install django
	> django-admin --version(will get version of django)
6. create a new diractory 
7. comes to diractory 
8. > django-admin startproject Amit
9. > cd Amit
9. > python manage.py runserver
	